title: 303.1 Semester Project:Extending DIPY’s Generalized Q-ball Imaging model to make predictions
text:
This project is part of the 303.1 semester project course.
The goal is to contribute to the DIPY framework by extending the Generalized Q-ball Imaging (GQI) model with predictive capabilities.
The key objectives are:

Implementing a predict() function to the GeneralizedQSamplingFit class
Thoroughly documenting the new code
Providing comprehensive and meaningful tests
Getting the prediction pull request accepted by DIPY

title: Implementation Report: Predict Function
text:
This report provides an overview of the implemented predict function, covering its purpose, operational mechanics, testing methodology, capabilities, and future directions.
Key topics include:

Functionality and operation of the predict function
Testing procedures applied to the function
Enabled applications and subsequent development steps

title: Report
section: Mathematical Foundations of the Predict Function
text:
Mathematical Foundations of the Predict Function
The predict function in the GeneralizedQSamplingFit class implements the inverse operation of the Orientation Distribution Function (ODF) reconstruction in Generalized Q-Sampling Imaging (GQI). It predicts the diffusion-weighted signal given a fitted ODF and a gradient table.

ODF Reconstruction
In GQI, the ODF \(\psi(\mathbf{u})\) is reconstructed from the diffusion signal \(\mathbf{S}\) using the kernel matrix \(\mathbf{K}\):
\(\psi = \mathbf{K}^T \mathbf{S}\)
where \(\mathbf{K}\) is the GQI kernel matrix of shape \((N_g, N_v)\), with \(N_g\) gradients and \(N_v\) sphere vertices.


Signal Prediction
To predict the signal \(\mathbf{S}'\) from the ODF \(\psi\) for a new gradient table, we solve the linear system:
\(\mathbf{K}'^T \mathbf{S}' = \psi\)
This is typically an overdetermined system. The solution uses regularization with Tikhonov regularization:
\(\mathbf{S}' = (\mathbf{K}' \mathbf{K}'^T + \lambda \mathbf{I})^{-1} \mathbf{K}' \psi\)
where \(\lambda\) is a small regularization parameter (INVERSE_LAMBDA = 1e-6).
In the code, the prediction_kernel function computes the matrix \((\mathbf{K}' \mathbf{K}'^T + \lambda \mathbf{I})^{-1} \mathbf{K}'\), and the full prediction involves composing with the original kernel for the fitted data.
The predicted signal is clamped to non-negative values to ensure physical validity.

title: Implementation Report: Predict Function
text: This report details the implementation of the predict function in the Generalized Q-Sampling Imaging (GQI) framework within DIPY. The function enables the prediction of diffusion-weighted signals from fitted Orientation Distribution Functions (ODFs), supporting advanced diffusion MRI analysis and simulation.
